    "Ruckman, Dr. Peter S_": "Verses 3\u20134 are self explanatory. The old saying is \u201cFools rush in where angels fear to tread\u201d (vss. 5\u20136). John `[char_John_Ref]`, evidently, is a younger man than Peter `[char_Peter_Mat_4]`; he certainly could run faster (vs. 4). \u201cSaw the linen clothes lying\u201d (vs. 5). The Catholic spook\u2019s ghostly clothes ( The Shroud of Turin ) are noticeably absent as most Roman Catholic junk is: a feather from the wing of the Holy Ghost, enough pieces of the cross in Europe to build a ranch-style house, four skulls of John the Baptist, some of Mary `[char_Mary_Ref]`\u2019s \u201cmilk,\u201d Christ\u2019s \u201cdiapers,\u201d part of the tablecloth of the \u201cLast Supper,\u201d and similar depraved, godless, pagan, fetish elements\u2014\u201cthe spear of Longinus,\u201d the \u201cHoly Grail,\u201d etc. (see The History of the New Testament Church, 1982, Vol. I, pp. 116, 319, and Here I Stand, Roland Bainton, Abingdon Cokesbury, 1950). Here, the Holy Spirit records a number of \u201citems\u201d which were mentioned on purpose to show you that the standard, Judaistic lie of Matthew 28:11\u201315 was a lie, obtained by a BRIBE. The lie had to do with God\u2019s Son\u2014reinforced and approved of by the Koran, which claims Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` never DIED, at all, on the cross (Sura 3:54, 5:75)\u2014so no one would believe that He \u201crose from the dead.\u201d That identical lie is propagated today by all orthodox Jews and Moslems; with the exception that some Moslems teach (three conflicting theories!) that He died a natural death later at the age of 127 in India, or He was raptured with Mary `[char_Mary_Ref]`. One hellhole is as good as another. In order to assist Mohammed and the rabbis, the NASV, NKJV, NRSV, and NIV have removed the word \u201cinfallible\u201d from Acts 1:3, since the translators of those four vulgar counterfeits didn\u2019t believe the proofs for Christ\u2019s resurrection were \u201cinfallible.\u201d (See comments on Acts 1:3 in that Commentary. Typical Conservative and Evangelical \u201cscholarship\u201d in the twentieth century: rotten as dead shrimp in a lost tackle box. )"
