    "Ruckman, Dr. Peter S_": "How did the disciples steal the body (Matt. 28:13) when it was guarded by Roman soldiers (Matt. 27:66)?\n1. Normal human beings cannot pass through closed doors.\n1. Three: neither blockheaded dumbbell could follow up his own exegesis, for Christ\u2019s disciples were clinging to Him the same morning He told Mary `[char_Mary_Ref]` not to \u201cTOUCH\u201d Him, and He did NOT \u201creturn to be with them forever.\u201d He left in forty days. Peekaboo! Rudolph the red-nosed ratfink! Do you know what you are dealing with in the twenty-first century? Bat brains gone bugs on pixie dust; they pose as \u201cgodly Biblical scholars.\u201d Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ would not allow ANY sinner to \u201ctouch him\u201d\u2014as in \u201cTOUCH\u201d \u2014until He had reported back home into the Holy of Holies (Heb. 9:11\u201312), for He had just lived a sinless life and died a sinless death, paying for sins. He had just dumped those sins in Hell (Acts 2:27, 31; Eph. 4:8\u201312) and was reporting back \u201cwithout sin\u201d (Heb. 9:28) from His finished work (John `[char_John_Ref]` 19:30). Which explains why Hebrews 9:28 and Ephesians 4:9\u2014\u201clower earthly regions\u201d ( NIV )\u2014have been messed with in the RV, RSV, NRSV, ASV, NASV, NIV, and similar apostate, counterfeit Bibles. Jerry Falwell takes this position against the King James Bible ( Liberty Bible Commentary, p. 697, citing some backslidden apostate named \u201cHughes\u201d). Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ went up beyond Alpha Draconis and back down to earth in less than four hours \u2014probably less than two hours. When He reports back, anyone can touch Him or cling to Him or shake hands with Him or slap Him on the back. The commentators were just so infected with unbelief they couldn\u2019t put any of the verses together. Not one of them connected Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ\u2019s trip into outer space mentioned in Ephesians 4:8\u201310 and Colossians 2:15 with John `[char_John_Ref]` 20:17, but that is when it took place. Only some of the bodies of Old Testament saints showed up Saturday night, AFTER 6 PM (see comments on Matt. 27 in that Commentary), but all of the souls went up. Any middle school teenager would have grasped the truth that Christ had to ascend right through the middle of a space filled with the populace listed in Ephesians 6:\n1. Modern science could easily be at least 999,000,000 light years off their speedometers, and\n1. The \u201clast Adam `[char_Adam_Luk_3]`,\u201d like the first Adam `[char_Adam_Luk_3]` (1 Cor. 15:45), is concerned about EATING. The term \u201ceat\u201d or \u201ceaten\u201d occurs sixteen times before you have read four chapters in your Bible. It is found fourteen times in one chapter (chap. 3), which is better than two times per verse!\n1. You were told, at the beginning of the BOOK, that the Author of the Book was the only correct interpreter (Gen. 41:16).\n1. A body that would materialize and dematerialize at will.\n1. He is to feed every born-again, Bible-believing Christian on the planet.\n1. The reference is to John `[char_John_Ref]` witnessing all of the events that take place at the Second Advent (see a preview of this in the comments under Matt. 16:28 and 17:1\u201310)."
