    "Ruckman, Dr. Peter S_": "If they did, why did they take time to unwrap the grave clothes when their lives depended upon getting out of there as fast as they could?\n2. Normal human beings cannot appear and disappear in a matter of seconds (Luke 24).\n2. They may be cockeyed on their \u201cmaximum speed\u201d for light, and\n2. The \u201cdiet\u201d\u2014where it deals with what we call \u201cmeat\u201d \u2014is FISH, exactly as it is in His post-resurrection appearance in Galilee (John `[char_John_Ref]` 21). No \u201csign of the fish\u201d\u2014see any corrupt Christian or Charismatic \u201chistorian\u201d\u2014has any connection with Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ at all. He EATS fish, serves them (John `[char_John_Ref]` 6:9), and likens Himself to be swallowed by one of them (Jonah 2:1\u20133; Matt. 12:40). He purposely got rid of their representative (see Ezek. 28:14) from \u201cover the throne\u201d (Isa. 14:11\u201314; Ezek. 28:14) so that only wild animals (a lion), domesticated mammals (an ox), and flying animals (an eagle) are represented before the throne (see Rev. 4; Ezek. 1, 10). Again, ditch all of the commentators and all the \u201cChristian historians.\u201d They think and write like blind men in a stupor. Having rejected the living words (John `[char_John_Ref]` 6:63) of the living God (John `[char_John_Ref]` 6:67), HE REJECTED THEM (see 1 Sam. 15:26 for details). If there were a \u201csign of a fish\u201d in a catacomb, it would be from departed worshippers of the fish god (\u201cDagon\u201d) who still wear his \u201cheaddress\u201d at every meeting of Catholic bishops and archbishops in Rome.\n2. You were told in the middle of the BOOK that the Author of the Book was the only correct interpreter (Dan. 2:26\u201330).\n2. A body that would pass through solid objects.\n2. He is to feed them non-biblical, anti-scriptural \u201ctraditions,\u201d right and left, whenever he wants to nullify things like Matthew 23:9; 1 Timothy 2:15, and Hebrews 10:10 found in the \u201cHOLY SCRIPTURES.\u201d\n2. You see, John `[char_John_Ref]` DOES tarry till Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` comes: he is present at the Second Advent. (See comments under Rev. 1:10 and 1:19 in that Commentary.)"
